Game: Blackjack<br>
Object of the game: Closest to 21 without going over wins.<br>
Played with: 1 decks of random numbers from 0-13, and 4 of each number in each deck. 0 (aka Ace) can be used as a 10 or 11. The numbers 11-13 represent face cards 11=Jack, 12=Queen, and 13=King.<br>
Number of participants: 1-4 + dealer (probably best with 2 players and dealer)<br>
Betting: Max bet 20pp<br>
RL rules used: Atlantic City rules. Blackjack without DOUBLE DOWN and SPLIT just to simplify the game.<br>
<br>
Game sequence: <br>
1. Each player announces his bet amount in /say or /gsay. Players give bets to dealer. (Dealer keeps track of the bets, so this will require pencil/paper)<br>
2. Dealer randomizes numbers 0-10 to each of the players.<br>
3. Dealer randomizes a number 0-10 for them self.<br>
4. Dealer randomizes another set of numbers to each player.<br>
5. Each player is given the opportunity to Hit/Stand<br>
6. If a player chooses to Hit, then another number is randomized for them. That person may Hit until they bust or say Stand.<br>
7. If a player chooses to Stand, nothing is done and dealer goes to next person.<br>
8. Dealer then randomizes his/her next number and can hit until they reach 16. Dealers are required to hit on anything below 16 and must stand once 17 or higher is reached.<br>
9. If Dealer is closest to 21 then the dealer keeps the bets that were placed by the players.<br>
10. A Chance (aka Blacjack) is hit by getting a 21 on the first two random numbers. The person scoring the Chance will receive their bet back plus half. (ex: bet 20pp they will receive 30pp). <br>
11. If no Chance is scored, but player beats the dealer they receive their bet back(ex: bet 20pp they will receive 20pp)<br>
